OL,6,FEggleton was sentenced to five and a
OL,7,Fhalf years in prison at Swindon Crown
OL,8,FCourt on Thursday 1 August after being
OL,9,Ffound guilty following a trial in
OL,10,FJanuary.
OL,12,FDetective Constable Aaron Rowe said:
OL,13,F"This was a long and complex case
OL,14,Fwhere Eggleton was trusted by his
OL,15,FAuntie Lilian who he then took
OL,16,Fadvantage of. What is even worse is
OL,17,Fthat sadly, Lilian passed away before
OL,18,Fgetting justice.
